#quiz-view.col-lg-8.offset-lg-2.col-md-12.col-sm-12.col-xs-12
  %h2 Quiz Instructions

  .card
    .card-header Please read the following instructions carefully:
    .card-body
      %ul
        %li
          The quizzes consists of questions carefully designed to help you self-assess your comprehension of the information presented on the topics covered in the module.
        %li  
          Each question in the quiz is of multiple-choice or "true or false" format. Read each question carefully, and click on the button next to your response that is based on the information covered on the topic in the module. Each correct or incorrect response will result in appropriate feedback immediately at the bottom of the screen.
        %li
          After responding to a question, click on the "Next" button at the bottom to go to the next questino.
        %li
          If you select an incorrect response for a question, you can try again until you get the correct response. If you retake the quiz, the questions and their respective responses will be randomized.
        %li
          The total score for the quiz is based on your responses to all questions. If you respond incorrectly to a question or retake a question and get the correct response, your quiz score will reflect it appropriately. However, your quiz will not be graded, if you skip a question or exit before responding to all the questions.
    .card-footer
      .row
        .col
          = link_to "Study", @study_path , class: 'btn btn-primary btn-sm btn-block', 'data-turbolinks': false
        .col

          = link_to "#{(@attempts.nil? or @attempts == 0) ? "Take a " : "Continue "} Quiz", @quiz_path , class: 'btn btn-dark btn-sm btn-block', 'data-turbolinks': false

        - if @attempts.present? and @attempts != 0
          .col
            = link_to "Take a New Quiz", @exam_path, data: { confirm: "Are you sure to start New Quiz? Your previous progess shall be lost." } , class: 'btn btn-warning btn-sm btn-block', 'data-turbolinks': false        
        - if current_user.present?
          .col
            = link_to "Result History", @result_path , class: 'btn btn-info btn-sm btn-block', 'data-turbolinks': false